title: NASDAQ Composite Falls 0.03% to 15095.14 — Data Talk | Morningstar
text:
The NASDAQ Composite Index is down 4.04 points or 0.03% today to 15095.14
--Largest one-day point and percentage decline since Wednesday, Dec 20, 2023
--Snaps a four-trading-day winning streak
--Off 5.99% from its record close of 16057.44 hit Friday, Nov. 19, 2021
--Up 35.25% from the Election Day close of 11160.57 on Tuesday, Nov. 3, 2020
--Up 12.17% from the Inauguration Day close of 13457.25 on Wednesday, Jan. 20, 2021
--Today's closing value is the second highest this year
--Off 0.03% from its 52-week high of 15099.18 hit Wednesday, Dec. 27, 2023
--Up 46.48% from its 52-week low of 10305.24 hit Thursday, Jan. 5, 2023
--Rose 44.06% from 52 weeks ago
--Off 0.03% from its 2023 closing high of 15099.18 hit Wednesday, Dec 27, 2023
--Up 46.48% from its 2023 closing low of 10305.24 hit Thursday, Jan. 5, 2023
--Month-to-date it is up 6.11%
--Year-to-date it is up 4628.65 points or 44.22%
Data based on preliminary market closing values
Source: Dow Jones Market Data, FactSet
(END) Dow Jones Newswires
